1 unit(s) Kidney Beans
85 g Tortilla Chips
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
113 g Mirepoix
2 unit(s) Green Onion
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
mL Crushed Tomatoes
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
2 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 unit(s) Vegetable Broth Concentrate
2 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 tsp Chipotle Powder
250 g Ground Beef
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.06 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Oil*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.
Thinly slice green onions.

Heat a large pot over medium heat.
When the pot is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then beef, mirepoix and peppers.
Cook, stirring often, until veggies start to soften and beef is cooked through 4-5 min.** Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, drain and rinse beans.

Add Mexican Seasoning and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) chipotle powder to the pot with veggies. ( NOTE: Reference heat guide.)
Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min.

Add crushed tomatoes, beans, broth concentrate and 3/4 cup (1 1/2 cups) water to the pot. Bring to a boil over high.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until chili thickens slightly, 12-15 min.
Season with pepper, to taste.

Divide veggie and beef chili between bowls.
Dollop sour cream over top, then sprinkle with cheese and green onions.
Serve half the tortilla chips (all for 4 ppl) alongside for dipping.

If you've opted to add beef, when the pan is hot, add beef along with mirepoix, and peppers. Cook, stirring often, until veggies soften slightly and beef is cooked through 4-5 min.** Follow the rest of the recipe as written.